				\begin{document}$${\text{f }}\left( {\text{x}} \right) = \sum ({\text{Fci}}({\text{Wi}})S)$$\end{document}fx=∑(Fci(Wi)S)where f(x) is either total water use (sap flow) or total ET in mm/day over the whole study area; Fci is fractional cover at pixel level i, Wi is water use either from sap flow or stand ET at 100% canopy cover, and S is a pixel size of 225 m2.
